cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with visual dialog, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves question generation and answering, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of discriminative methods suggests the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the assessment of system performance suggests the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
